Detractors should stop evaluating bitcoin in its infancy and saying bitcoin is terrible money. Look at the price swings and lack of acceptance. Bitcoin has intrinsic properties of a great monetary asset but only becomes good money after widespread adoption.

A serious error that both bitcoiners and detractors often make is to confuse bitcoin as it is now with bitcoin in its final state of adoption. No one can seriously think that an asset that has wild price swings and 0.5% adoption makes for good money.
